Jessica Parker

When you look into my eyes you say it’s all going to be okay But I know you hide too never reveal what you go through sun shines on a brighter day now it’s ominous, gloomy, grey I wander on a darkened night and you follow close, but out of sight you’re the reason I wander, so I stray from the regular path of a normal way Do you wander too? I don’t know River streams start to flow You’re enveloped in darkness; you’ve been revived Thank God for you to be alive. But what is actual is not real How then do you really feel? You followed my path on that night long ago when the river streams flowed and flow Truth can hurt so I want to protect Plagued by some hideous defect littered with flaws which threaten the strength to hide what is present, I go to great length dig a hole, you will not find the creeping shadows in my mind i will deceive before i’ll show i will not reap what i have sown my hands are tied, but not my will a cup in the rain that will not fill i do what it takes to win the prize no matter the hearts; no matter the lies don’t stop now. We’re on a roll. x marks a spot on my soul seek or don’t seek, both i fear the closer you are, the more that is clear A noble steed black as pitch will rescue me from some confinement or some ditch the clothes on your back you willingly shed when deep in my bones the cold infects Ill hide away between the branches of a tree caution floats among the breeze wait and see. Wait and see. do you know what you do to me?
